       Noncommercial Academic Research.

1.4 "Organization" includes any company, corporation, partnership, nonprofit
organization, nongovernmental organization, charity, foundation, association,
government body, laboratory, institution, or other legal entity.

1.5 "Commercial Use" means any use intended for, connected with, or reasonably
likely to result in commercial advantage, monetary compensation, revenue,
business operations, paid services, product development, internal corporate
research, customer delivery, or other financial benefit.

1.6 "Competitive Use" means using the Materials to develop, train, test,
benchmark, evaluate, improve, support, or market a product, service, model, or
system that competes or may compete with a product, service, model, research
project, or system of the copyright holder.

